      "body_md": "## AuditToolkit macOS Security Lite — v0.1.0\n\nRead-only macOS host security audit tool. **Developer-ID signed, Apple-notarised, and\nstapled** — installs Gatekeeper-clean on any Mac with no override.\n\n### Artifacts\n| File | Notes |\n| --- | --- |\n| `AuditToolkit-macOS-Security-Lite-0.1.0.pkg` | Installer package (notarised + stapled) |\n| `AuditToolkit-macOS-Security-Lite-0.1.0.dmg` | Disk image / drag-install (notarised + stapled) |\n| `SHA256SUMS` | Integrity checksums |\n| `README.md` / `CHANGELOG.md` | Release docs |\n\n### Trust\nSigned by **Developer ID: Michael Churchill (Team ID `ZXPT7W8AST`)**, notarised by Apple.\nVerified before release: `spctl --assess --type install` → **accepted, source=Notarized\nDeveloper ID**; `stapler validate` passes on both artifacts.\n\n```bash\nsudo installer -pkg AuditToolkit-macOS-Security-Lite-0.1.0.pkg -target /\naudittoolkit-macos-security-lite run\n```\n\nCompletes the v0.1.0 trio alongside Linux Host Lite and Windows Security Lite.\n",
